.SUBTITLE   ANGLE__INTERVAL command
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*ANGLE__INTERVAL \*

.INDEX SLOPES> commands> ANGLE__INTERVAL
.INDEX SLOPES> ANGLE__INTERVAL command
.LM +8
.P0; Sets the angular step value for aspect calculation.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		ANGLE_INTERVAL   angular_interval
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LM +8
.P-8;angular__interval
.p 0;An integer value specifying a whole number of degrees.
The default value is 30 degrees.
.LM -8
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.p 0;ANGLE__INTERVAL is used to define the angular step value for ASPECT 
calculation. If output to a graphics device has been selected with the
ENABLE GRAPHICS command then each angular step is displayed in a different 
colour.
.p0; If output is to a DTI file then if the ENABLE CLASSIFY command has been 
given, each classified index is output to the DTI file. 
eg. if an angular step of 10 degrees is specified then aspect values of 1 to 
10 degrees would be output to the DTI file with a value of 1, 11 to 20 
degrees with  a value of 2 etc.
.p0
If the ENABLE CLASSIFY command is not specified then the ANGLE__INTERVAL 
command has no effect on the output to a DTI file.
.p 0
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following error messages are specific to the ANGLE__INTERVAL command.
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ANGLE_INTERVAL
Command requires an integer value between 3 and 360

.END LIT
.P 0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.p0;SLOPES>^*ANGLE__INTERVAL 20<CR>\*
