.SUBTITLE   ASPECT command
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*ASPECT\*

.INDEX SLOPES> commands> ASPECT
.INDEX SLOPES> ASPECT command

.LM +8
.P0; Calculates and displays an ASPECT map.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		ASPECT
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\* _None
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.p 0;
This command calculates an ASPECT map indicating the direction of SLOPE 
at each node in the DTM.
Aspect is measured in degrees clockwise from north (ie east = 90 degrees, 
west = 270 degrees). 
.p0;Further information on the ASPECT algorithm used is given in the 
Description section.
.p0
The aspect information is either displayed on the graphics screen, if the 
ENABLE GRAPHICS command has been given and/or to a DTI file if the FILEOUT
command has been issued.
.p0
If output to a graphics device is selected then either a grey or colour 
image is produced depending on whether the ENABLE GREY command has been given.
By default a colour image is produced. The displayed step intervals are 
controlled by the ANGLE__INTERVAL command.
.p0; If output is to a DTI file then if the ENABLE CLASSIFY has been given
each classified index, as defined by the ANGLE__INTERVAL command  is output to
the DTI file. For example, if an angular step of 10 degrees is specified then
aspect values of 1 to 10 degrees are output to the DTI file with a value of 1,
11 to 20 degrees with  a value of 2 etc. Otherwise the actual calculated
aspect values are output. 
.p0
ASPECT information is only calculated for matrix nodes lying within the
currently defined WINDOW. 
.P0
Typing <CTRL/C> (Pressing the Ctrl and C keys together) aborts the calculation 
and display of ASPECT.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following error messages are specific to the ASPECT command.
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ASPECT 
Output medium not specified
Use ENABLE GRAPHICS or FILEOUT commands

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ASPECT 
No input DTI file had been specified

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ASPECT 
DATA_TYPE BYTE illegal for ASPECT output

.END LIT
.P 0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.p0;SLOPES>^*ASPECT<CR>\*
.BR;SLOPES>
.bl
.FILL
.!******************************************************************************
.PAGE
.SUBTITLE   CENTRE command
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*CENTRE \*

.INDEX SLOPES> commands> CENTRE
.INDEX SLOPES> CENTRE command
.LM +8
.P0; Centres the current display around the specified DTI matrix point.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		CENTRE x_coord y_coord
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LM +8
.P-8;x__coord y__coord
.P0; The matrix coordinates specified as a column and row value. 2 integer 
values are required.
.LM -8
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.p 0;The displayed image is centred around the screen position corresponding
to the supplied matrix x y coordinate point provided they lie within the
geographical bounds of the file.

.p0
This command has effect only on a graphics device which supports
hardware pixel replication. 
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following error messages are specific to the CENTRE command.
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command CENTRE
A graphics device is not selected

*** ERROR *** Specifying command CENTRE
Command requires 1 DTI x,y coord pair

.END LIT
.P 0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.p0;SLOPES>^*CENTRE 100 100<CR>\*
.BR;SLOPES>
.bl
.FILL

