.SUBTITLE   COLOURS command
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*COLOURS\*

.INDEX SLOPES> commands> COLOURS
.INDEX SLOPES> COLOURS command

.LM +8
.P0; Defines the colour entry that is to be associated with the value steps.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		COLOURS I1 I2 ...I7
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LM +8
.P-8;I1 I2 ...I7
.P0; The colour index values to be associated with the value steps.
Up to seven integer values may be specified in the range 1 to 127.
.LM -8
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.p0
The COLOUR command allows the colour indices associated with step values to 
be reassigned. 
.lit
eg. 
	COLOURS 3 12 7

.end lit
allocates colours 3,12 and 7 in the colour table to the first three gradient 
steps in a slope map. 
.p0
The command applies only to SLOPE and  HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE maps. If 
the ENABLE CLASSIFY command has been given, then the colour index values
are output to the DTI file.
.p0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following error messages are specific to the COLOURS command.
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command COLOURS
Command requires between 1 and 7 colour index values

*** ERROR *** Specifying command COLOURS
Colour values should be in the range 1 to 127

.END LIT
.P 0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.p0;SLOPES>^*COLOURS 2 5 20<CR>\*
.BR;SLOPES>
.bl
.FILL

