.INDEX SLOPES> DATA__TYPE command

.LM +8
.p 0;Sets the data type for the output file.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		DATA_TYPE keyword
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command Parameters: \* 
.LM +8
.P-8;keyword
.P0; The data type chosen from one of the following:
.lit

	BYTE
	WORD
	LONGWORD
	REAL

.end lit
.p0;The default data type is WORD.
.LM -8
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.p0
The DATA__TYPE command is used to set the data type of the output DTI file
specified using the FILEOUT command.
.P0
Note that ASPECT maps may not be output if BYTE data type has been selected, 
unless ENABLE CLASSIFY has been specified.
.p0
The default data type is WORD.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*_None
.br;The following message is specific to the DATA__TYPE command.
.BLANK
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* specifying command DATA__TYPE
.br;Valid qualifier is BYTE, LONGWORD, REAL or WORD.
.p0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Example:\*
             
.P0;SLOPES>^*DATA__TYPE WORD<CR>\*
.BR;SLOPES>

