.SUBTITLE   DISABLE ABSOLUTE
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DISABLE ABSOLUTE\*
.INDEX SLOPES Commands> DISABLE ABSOLUTE
.INDEX SLOPES> DISABLE ABSOLUTE command

.LM +8
.P 0;Disables a previous ENABLE ABSOLUTE command. 
.LM -8

.P0
 ^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:	        DISABLE ABSOLUTE
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command Parameters: \* _None
.p0

^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.P 0;DISABLE ABSOLUTE cancels a previous ENABLE ABSOLUTE command.  If DISABLE
ABSOLUTE is given, then coordinate values required by the WINDOW command,
supplied in metre or projection units, must be specified as an offset from the
SW corner of the matrix. 

.BR; By default window values should be specified as absolute coordinates.
.p0 
The SHOW ENABLE command may be used to check the status  of the option.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.BLANK
.br;The following message is specific to the DISABLE command.
.BLANK
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* Specifying command DISABLE
.BR;Command qualifiers are ABSOLUTE, AVERAGE, CLEAR, 
.BR;CLASSIFY, GRAPHICS, GREYSCALE, LEGEND, NULL__BORDER, PERCENT, 
.BR;RECENTRE, TABLE or TEXT
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.P0;SLOPES>^*DISABLE ABSOLUTE<CR>\*
.br;SLOPES>

