.PAGE
.SUBTITLE   FILEIN
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*FILEIN\*
.INDEX SLOPES Commands> FILEIN
.INDEX SLOPES> FILEIN command

.LM +8
.p 0; Opens and maps into memory a DTI file.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:	        FILEIN  file-spec
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LM +8
.P-8;file-spec
.P0; The file specification for the input DTI file. Any part of the file 
specification not supplied is taken from the default 'LSL$DTI:DTI.DTI'
.LM -8
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.p 0;This command opens and maps into memory a DTI file.
.br; Details derived from the header of the file are displayed on the terminal
to confirm that the file has been successfully opened. 
.p0 
.p 0;If the logical name LSL$MATRIX__DEFAULT__WINDOW is defined with a value of
"1", then a default area of interest defined in matrix units of bottom left
hand corner 1,1 and top right hand corner 200,200 is set when the file is
opened. If the logical name is absent or has any other value,  or if the input
DTI file has fewer than 200 columns or 200 rows, then a default window
equivalent to the total matrix is set.
.p0
The area of interest may be altered at any time by use of the WINDOW command.
.p0
If the rotation value (DTI__ORDER__CORNER) 
held in the header of the DTI file is not the default,
(south west) then a warning message is output when the file is opened. 

.p 0;Information on the mapped DTI file may be obtained at any time 
by typing 'SHOW FILES'.
.p0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.BLANK
.br;The following messages are specific to the FILEIN command.
.BLANK
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* Specifying command FILEIN
.br;Filename is missing

.TP 15
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Example:\*
             
.P0;SLOPES>^*FILEIN TEST<CR>\*
.lit

File    :  LSL$DTI:TEST.DTI
Header  :  LSLA Data:  WORD

Units are DTI Matrix Value

Matrix Coverage   SW:     1      1  NE:   301   251
Matrix Window     SW:     1      1  NE:   301   251
Matrix Interval    E:     1          N:     1
Value Range         :     0    to    851
.end lit
SLOPES>

.!******************************************************************************
.PAGE
.SUBTITLE FILEOUT command
.INDEX SLOPES> commands> FILEOUT
.INDEX SLOPES> FILEOUT command
.P0
^^^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^^^*FILEOUT\*

.LEFT MARGIN +8
.P 0;Specifies the file-spec of the DTI file is to receive SLOPE, ASPECT, 
HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE or SHADE DTI data.
.LEFT MARGIN -8

.P0
^^^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*FORMAT:	FILEOUT  file-spec\*
.P0
^^^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^^^*COMMAND PARAMETERS:\*
.LEFT MARGIN +8
.P-8;file-spec
.BLANK
.P 0;The file-spec of the DTI file which is to receive the derived data.

.P 0;Any parts of the file-spec not supplied for the FILEOUT command will be 
taken from the default file specification 'LSL$DTI:DTI.SLP;0'.
.LEFT MARGIN -8
.P0
^^^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^^^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.P 0
The FILEOUT command specifies the name of the DTI file which is to
receive the calculated SLOPE, ASPECT, HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE or SHADE data. The
file is closed after calculations have taken place. 
.p0
Note that output may take place both to the DTI file and the graphics screen 
if the ENABLE GRAPHICS command has also been given.
.P0
^^^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^^^*Messages:\*

.P 0;The following messages are specific to the FILEOUT command:

.BLANK
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* Specifying command FILEOUT
.br;Filename is missing

.FILL
.P0
^^^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^^^*Examples:\*
.BLANK
.BR;SLOPES> ^^^*FILEOUT DUA3:[DEMONSTRATION]IDAHO_<CR_>\*
.BR;SLOPES>

.!******************************************************************************
.PAGE
.SUBTITLE   HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE command
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE\*

.INDEX SLOPES> commands> HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE
.INDEX SLOPES> HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE command

.LM +8
.P0; Calculates and displays a height difference map.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		HEIGHT_DIFFERENCE
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*_None
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.p 0;
This command calculates a height difference map indicating the difference
 in height between each DTM node and its neighbours. If the ENABLE AVERAGE
command has been given then the average height difference is output. Otherwise
the maximum height difference is calculated.
.p0
Output is displayed on the graphics screen if
ENABLE GRAPHICS command has been given and/or to a DTI file if the FILEOUT
command has been issued.
.p0
HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE information is only calculated matrix points that lie
within the currently defined WINDOW. 
.P0
Typing <CTRL/C> (Pressing the Ctrl and C keys together) aborts the 
calculation and display of height difference.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following error messages are specific to the HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE command.
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command HEIGHT_DIFFERENCE
Output medium not specified
Use ENABLE GRAPHICS or FILEOUT commands

*** ERROR *** Specifying command HEIGHT_DIFFERENCE
No input DTI file had been specified

.END LIT
.P 0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.p0;SLOPES>^*HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE<CR>\*
.BR;SLOPES>
.!******************************************************************************
