.SUBTITLE   LUT
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*LUT\*
.INDEX SLOPES Commands> LUT
.INDEX SLOPES> LUT command

.LM +8
.p 0; Selects and makes current the specified colour table.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:	        LUT  [keyword] file-spec
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LM +8
.P-8;keyword
.p0; The SLOPES option to which the look up table refers. Valid options are:-
.lit

		ASPECT
		HEIGHT_DIFFERENCE
		SLOPE
		SHADE
.END LIT
.P-8;file-spec
.P0; The file specification for the new colour table. Any part of the file
specification not supplied will be taken from the default LSL$LOOKUP:.DAT.
.LM -8
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.P0; This command is used to read in a new look up colour table. 
The colour table is a file containing the RGB definitions for a series of
colour values. These values are used when images are displayed on the 
screen. 
If the optional keyword argument is omitted, then the specified
colour table is read in immediately.
.p0
The keyword argument is used to to specify the colour table to be used 
when subsequent SLOPE, ASPECT, SHADE or HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE maps are
generated on the graphics screen.

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.BLANK
.br;The following message is specific to the LUT command.
