.SUBTITLE  STEP
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*STEP\*
.INDEX SLOPES Commands> STEP
.INDEX SLOPES> STEP command

.LM +8
.P 0;Defines a series of value step intervals.
.p0
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		 STEP values[...]
.end lit
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LM +8
.P-8;values
.p 0;One or more step interval values. Up to 7 integer values
 may be specified. At least one value is required.
.LM -8
.p0	
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.p0; This command divides the calculated values for the SLOPE and
HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE commands,   
into a series of steps which are displayed in different colours. 
A single value denotes a constant step interval, while
a variable step interval may be defined by entering up to 7 values.
A particular colour index may be associated with each step by means of the
COLOUR command.
.p0;The default value is a step of 5.
.p0
The colour index that will be associated with each step may 
by examined by means of the command SHOW SLOPE or SHOW HEIGHT__DIFFERENCE.
.p0
.tp 20
.p0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.BLANK
.br;The following messages are specific to the STEP command.
.BLANK
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* Specifying command STEP
.br;Command requires between 1 and 7 integer values
.blank
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* Specifying command STEP
.br;Command requires integer values in the range 1 to "upper-value"
.blank
.br;_*_*_* WARNING _*_*_* Value range exceeded
.br;step "step_number" is truncated to "DTI-value"
.blank

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*

.P0;SLOPES>^*STEP 10<CR>\*
.br;SLOPES>^*STEP 1 2 3 5 10 10 10 <CR>\*
.br;SLOPES>
