.SUBTITLE UNITS command
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*UNITS\*
.INDEX SLOPES Commands> UNITS
.INDEX SLOPES> UNITS command

.LEFT MARGIN +8
.P 0;Specifies the units of measurement that will be used when defining an area
of interest in the input DTI file.
.LEFT MARGIN -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*FORMAT:                UNITS units\*


.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LEFT MARGIN +8
.P-8;units
.P 0;A keyword defining the measurement units, chosen from: 
.LIT

	MATRIX	   Matrix grid interval units, i.e rows and columns
	METRES	   Metre offsets from the south west corner of the DTI file
	SECONDS    Latitude and Longitude in seconds of arc
	LATLONG	   Latitude and Longitude in degrees, minutes and seconds
        PROJECTION Projection Record Units (eg. mms on the source document)

.END LIT
.LEFT MARGIN -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.P 0;The UNITS command defines the units of measurement that will be used when
defining an area of interest in the currently selected DTI file
 by means of the WINDOW command.
.br;The command also controls in what format details from the header of the
DTI file  are displayed, when the SHOW FILES command is given.
.P0;The command should be given after defining the an DTI file  since an
appropriate default units of measurement is set up when the file is opened. 
.p0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.BLANK
.br;The following messages are specific to the UNITS command.
.BLANK
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* Specifying command UNITS
.br;Command should be followed by MATRIX, METRES, LATLONG, SECONDS or PROJECTION
.br;Current setting is "units"
.blank
.br;_*_*_* ERROR _*_*_* Specifying command UNITS
.br;Command qualifier is invalid for the input file
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
.BLANK
.BR;SLOPES> ^*UNITS MATRIX_<CR_>\*
.BR;SLOPES>
.!******************************************************************************
