.LIT
FORMAT:	        ZSCALE scale_factor
.end lit
.p 0;
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LM +8
.P-8;scale__factor
.p 0;Scale__factor defines a z scaling factor that is applied to all DTM
height values.  A real value is required.
.LM -8
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.p 0;The ZSCALE command defines a vertical exaggeration (z scale) factor. This
is a value by which all DTM height values are multiplied before a slope, 
aspect or shaded map is generated.
.P 0;By default no vertical exaggeration is applied ie. a z scale factor of
1 is used.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following error messages are specific to the ZSCALE command:
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ZSCALE
Command requires 1 real argument

.END LIT
.P 0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.p0;SLOPES>^*ZSCALE 2.5\*
.br;SLOPES>

